you can use the `toMap` collector and provide a mergeFunction. 
`Collectors.toMap()` can be called with 3 parameters: first one is for mapping they key of the map, in our case the user id, so something like this `user -&gt; user.getId()` or simply `User::getId`. 

The second parameter is mapping the value, in our case we want to use the user itself as value, so we&#39;ll just pass `user -&gt; user`. 

Finally, the merge functions will be used for users this the same id (duplicates): in this case we want to create a new User that has all the subjects:

    private User mergeUsers(User user1, User user2) {
    	List&lt;String&gt; allSubjects = new ArrayList&lt;&gt;();
    	allSubjects.addAll(user1.getSubject());
    	allSubjects.addAll(user2.getSubject());
    	return new User(user1.getId(), user1.getName(), allSubjects);
    }

Now, let&#39;s stream the users and collect them as discussed:


    @Test
    void test2() {
    	//given
    	User user1 = new User(1, &quot;John&quot;, Arrays.asList(&quot;English&quot;));
    	User user2 = new User(2,&quot;Peter&quot;, Arrays.asList(&quot;English&quot;));
    	User user3 = new User(1, &quot;John&quot;, Arrays.asList(&quot;Chemistry&quot;));
    	List&lt;User&gt; users = List.of(user1, user2, user3);
    
    	//when
    	Map&lt;Integer, User&gt; usersById = users.stream()
    			.collect(Collectors.toMap(u-&gt; u.getId(), u -&gt; u, (u1, u2) -&gt; mergeUsers(u1, u2)));
    
    	//then
    	assertThat(usersById.get(1).getSubject())
    			.containsExactly(&quot;English&quot;, &quot;Chemistry&quot;);
    	assertThat(usersById.get(2).getSubject())
    			.containsExactly(&quot;English&quot;);
    }

ps: you can make small improvements, such as using method reference or encapsulating this logic of merging inside the User class:

    Map&lt;Integer, User&gt; usersById = users.stream()
    			.collect(Collectors.toMap(User::getId, user -&gt; user, User::merge));

read more about Colelctors.toMap and mergingFunction here: https://www.baeldung.com/java-collectors-tomap

