The good option is to use [AdminClient][1] as below before starting to produce or consume the messages

    private static final int ADMIN_CLIENT_TIMEOUT_MS = 5000;           
     try (AdminClient client = AdminClient.create(properties)) {
                client.listTopics(new ListTopicsOptions().timeoutMs(ADMIN_CLIENT_TIMEOUT_MS)).listings().get();
            } catch (ExecutionException ex) {
                LOG.error(&quot;Kafka is not available, timed out after {} ms&quot;, ADMIN_CLIENT_TIMEOUT_MS);
                return;
            }


  [1]: https://kafka.apache.org/11/javadoc/index.html?org/apache/kafka/clients/admin/AdminClient.html

